  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reviving the transport and marketing business in Chingola District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After a brief cooperation with CDCU in 2018 with one activity for strategic planning  in 2019 CDCU will receive additional support from Agriterra to revive its transport and marketing business.CDCU has 43 paid-up Primary Cooperative members  representing around 2 000 farmers in the district. CDCU runs a transport business focused on input distribution to members and crop marketing of members produce  particularly maize. Thanks to government contracts  CDCU was running profitably up to 2017. But due to government policy changes and truck failures  the business went down and now needs to be revived. Also  trucks needed repairs to be able to run again.BHAG 2019: A profitable transport amp marketing business with sound capitalisation  based on a SMART business plan  run by capable management and serving 56 commited member cooperatives that invest in the union.              The project will focus on activities to promote member commitment  increase capitalisation of the cooperative union  optimise business planning  strengthen financial management and improve the cooperative basics at member level.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CDCU to have a profitable transport  marketing business with sound capitalisation  run by capable management and supplied by commited member cooperatives that invest in the union.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">My.Coop training + ToT for a selection of viable  business-minded primary cooperatives
Mission tailor-made workshop on Internal Capitalisation  Member Commitment and Business Plan development
Basic Financial Management training
Exchange visit with Bulima cooperative (nearby Agriterra client) on the transport business</narrative>
  </description>
